# Refactoring for Complexity Reduction

The goal is to reduce the complexity of [health_synthesizer.py](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/Support/health_synthesizer.py) (18 -> <15) and [component_classifier.py](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/Support/component_classifier.py) (17 -> <15) to restore a 100% Health Index.

## Proposed Changes

### Support Agents

#### [MODIFY] [component_classifier.py](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/Support/component_classifier.py)

Replace the sequence of [if](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/scripts/lint_rule_engine.py#13-41) statements with a systematic pattern matcher using a list of rules. This reduces the number of branching nodes.

```python
    def map_type(self, rel_path: str) -> str:
        p = rel_path.lower()
        
        # Rule set to reduce cyclomatic complexity
        rules = [
            (lambda x: x.endswith("__init__.py"), "PACKAGE_MARKER"),
            (lambda x: "test" in x, "TEST"),
            (self._is_doc, "DOC"),
            (self._is_config, "CONFIG"),
            (lambda x: "core" in x or "domain" in x, "CORE"),
            (self._is_agent, "AGENT"),
            (lambda x: "util" in x or "helper" in x, "UTIL"),
            (self._is_interface, "INTERFACE"),
            (lambda x: "data" in x or "repository" in x, "DATA")
        ]
        
        for condition, result in rules:
            if condition(p): return result
        return "LOGIC"
```

